name: cis-4-cyclohexene-1,2-dicarboxylic anhydride
Reason: 4-Cyclohexene-1,2-dicarboxylic anhydride has a melting point that we can analyze by considering its structural components: (1) The cyclohexene ring itself contributes to the melting point due to its rigidity and molecular weight, estimated at around +20 °C. (2) The carboxylic acid and anhydride functionalities introduce a rigid structure with potential hydrogen bonding, estimated at around +10 °C each. (3) The presence of two phenyl groups can significantly increase the melting point due to the enhancement of the crystalline structure and the increase in molecular weight, estimated at around +20 °C each.
